datasets.name: 0de8967f
queryLines:
select
  data.tz
from values
  ('America/New_York'),
  ('America/Chicago'),
  ('America/Denver'),
  ('America/Los_Angeles') as data(tz)

datasets.name: 392b9798
queryLines:
SELECT *
FROM IDENTIFIER(CONCAT(:catalog_name, '.default.earthquake_data'))
WHERE time BETWEEN :time_parameter.min AND :time_parameter.max

datasets.name: d42bac49
queryLines:
select count(*) as total_magnitude_bucket
,magnitude_bucket from (select CASE
  WHEN mag < 2 THEN 'Micro (<2)'
  WHEN mag BETWEEN 2 AND 3 THEN 'Minor (2–3)'
  WHEN mag BETWEEN 3 AND 4 THEN 'Light (3–4)'
  ELSE 'Moderate+ (4+)'
END AS magnitude_bucket
from IDENTIFIER(CONCAT(:catalog_name, '.default.earthquake_data')) where time between :time_parameter.min and :time_parameter.max)

group by magnitude_bucket

datasets.name: edcadad0
queryLines:
SELECT 
  count(*) AS event_count,
  CASE 
    WHEN size(split(place, ', ')) = 1 THEN split(place, ', ')[0]
    ELSE split(place, ', ')[1]
  END AS country
FROM (
  SELECT 
     time,
    title,
    mag,
    longitude,
    place,
    latitude
  FROM IDENTIFIER(CONCAT(:catalog_name, '.default.earthquake_data')) where time between :time_parameter.min and :time_parameter.max
)
GROUP BY country

datasets.name: da53be09
queryLines:
select count(*) as total_dept_category,depth_category from (
select CASE
  WHEN depth < 10 THEN 'Shallow (<10km)'
  WHEN depth BETWEEN 10 AND 70 THEN 'Intermediate (10–70km)'
  ELSE 'Deep (>70km)'
END AS depth_category
from IDENTIFIER(CONCAT(:catalog_name, '.default.earthquake_data')) where time between :time_parameter.min and :time_parameter.max
) group by depth_category

datasets.name: f49b530c
queryLines:
SELECT
  CAST(time AS DATE)                 AS event_date,
  YEAR(time)                         AS year,
  MONTH(time)                        AS month,
  DAY(time)                          AS day,
  DATE_FORMAT(time, 'yyyy-MM')       AS year_month,
  DATE_FORMAT(time, 'yyyy-MM-dd')    AS year_month_day,
  WEEKOFYEAR(time)                   AS week_of_year,
  DAYOFWEEK(time)                    AS day_of_week,
  DATE_FORMAT(time, 'EEEE')          AS day_name,
  HOUR(time)                         AS hour
FROM default.earthquake_data;
